g.text: Be able to navigate the store quickly
Never sees enough employees on the floor
Hates it when the instore inventory doesn’t match the site

Marta is a caregiver with a passion for home repairs. When she isn’t with a patient, you can find Marta trying to patch a wall or remodeling her bathroom. As much as Marta loves home repairs, she knows she needs help in order to get it done. She needs one on one time with a knowledgeable employee so that she can feel confident with her projects. Every time she goes into Home Depot she finds herself roaming the aisles trying to find what she needs and getting lost in the process. When she finally finds an employee, she gets ignored. Marta is so frustrated that she decides to leave and goes to a local home repair store that can give her the kind of customer service she is looking for.
“I need personalized customer service so I feel confident I am starting a project off right.”
